                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Ambroise Vollard, Paris by November 1895 [this and the following information according to New York 2006-7]; Galerie Bernheim-Jeune, Paris, by July 1907; sold to Paul Cassirer, Berlin in July 1907; sold to Bernheim-Jeune, Paris in November 1908.  Jos Hessel, Paris by 1913 [based on inscription on reverse; see also New York Times 1913 and Borgmeyer 1913] and until at least 1920 [see Paris 1920].  Paul Rosenberg, Paris by 1922 [see Paris 1922]; sold to Frederick Clay Bartlett, Chicago [through Joseph Stransky of French Galleries, New York] by 1925; given to the Art Institute, 1926.</p>
